### Event card accuracy audit (data.py vs code)
Audit notes against `app/environments/cubalibre/envs/data.py` text (with explicit mismatches/caveats called out per card below).

Format: `Un:` unshaded effect/capability; `Sh:` shaded effect/capability; `Tests:` file references.

1. **Armored Cars (1)** — Un: choose 26July/DR; free March into chosen space (no Govt-presence restriction) from chosen adjacent source, then free Ambush there (even if Active). Sh: before Govt Assault, move Troops from any spaces into the Assault space via explicit pre-Assault reinforcement phase, then Assault resolves. Tests: `tests/cubalibre/test_cards_1_4.py`.
2. **Guantánamo Bay (2)** — Un: 26July may Kidnap in Sierra Maestra as if City (capability). Sh: until Propaganda, Air Strike removes 2 and allowed even if Embargoed (capability). Tests: `tests/cubalibre/test_card_2_guantanamo_bay.py`.
3. **Eulogio Cantillo (3)** — Un: free March "out" with normal multi-step choices (multiple destinations), moving 1 Guerrilla per destination pick until none remain, end on PASS. Tests: `tests/cubalibre/test_round3_events.py`, `tests/cubalibre/test_cantillo_unshaded_targeting.py`.
4. **S.I.M. (4)** — Un: select Support space with no Police; shift 1 level toward Neutral (Active Support→Passive Support→Neutral). Sh: capability allows Police to participate in Govt Sweep/Assault as if Troops (until next Propaganda). Tests: `tests/cubalibre/test_sim_unshaded_target_selection.py`, `tests/cubalibre/test_cards_1_4.py`.
5. **Rolando Masferrer (5)** — Un: set a Province with Troops and 1 adjacent Province to Passive Opposition. Sh: capability allows Sweep to free Assault 1 space as its Special Activity (until Propaganda). Tests: `tests/cubalibre/test_card_5_masferrer.py`.
6. **Sánchez Mosquera (6)** — Un: select Mountain; remove all Troops there to available. Sh: capability makes Assault in Mountains unrestricted (treat Mountain as City) until next Propaganda. Tests: `tests/cubalibre/test_card_6_mosquera.py`.
