## 13) Future Enhancements (Post-UI)

### Agent Piece Selection Within Spaces
Current behavior: when multiple pieces of the same faction exist in one space, selection is deterministic ("first available"):
- Terror: activates first Underground guerrilla.
- Pact of Miami: removes first available guerrilla.
- Other operations: similar deterministic priorities.

Enhancement: add UI-driven piece selection so agents can choose which specific piece to affect when multiple eligible pieces exist.

Requirements: UI layer to display/select individual pieces; new phase for piece selection with masking; adds strategic depth for cash management and faction-specific targeting.

Priority: Low (edge case; current behavior is acceptable and follows rulebook where specified).
